labels.name: bug

issue.body:
Many issues have been opened due to the fact that the types resolve to `never`. That is because they don't have `strictNullChecks` enabled.

In light of that, I think we should document the fact that this option is required in order to use the types from this repository

issue.title: Document that `strictNullChecks` is required to be enabled

labels.name: bug
labels.description: Something isn't working as documented, or is being fixed

issue.body:
Many issues have been opened due to the fact that the types resolve to `never`. That is because they don't have `strictNullChecks` enabled.

In light of that, I think we should document the fact that this option is required in order to use the types from this repository
